### Description

When passing an arrow function as Input to a Child Component using `InputSignal`, the function does not execute when called inside the Child Component. However, when using `@Input()`, it works as expected.

- Parent Component : 

```` typescript

@Component({
  selector: 'app-parent',
  imports: [ChildComponent],
  template: `
  <app-child [callback]="callback"></app-child>
  `,
})
export class ParentComponent {
  name = 'parent';
  callback = () => {
    console.log('from parent', this.name);
  };
}
````
- Child Component : 
```` typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-child',
  template: `
  <button (click)="callback()">button</button>
  `,
})
export class ChildComponent {
  callback: InputSignal<(() => void) | undefined> = input<() => void>();
  // @Input() callback: () => void = () => {}; <--- This Works
}
````


